MLC: IP to MPEG gateway.
Input: IP or DVB-ASI
Output: DVB-ASI


Based on UBR 72xx.
Each UBR can hold 4 line cards.
UBR uses MIPS as host processor.

MLC: 4 DSP daughter boards, 2 IO daughter boards, shared buffer (SDRAM)

DSP daughter board: 3 C6202 or 2 C64xx
IO daughter board: 6 DVB-ASI input, or 6 DVB-ASI output
                   Future interfaces: DHEI, QAM, Scrambler


Main difference between RateMux and MLC:
  RateMux
    - input TP demuxed into individual DSP private memory
    - no data sharing among DSP
    - output is through an output DSP, limited to 54 Mbps for C62 

  MLC
    - input demuxed into a big shared buffer
    - data sharing among DSP through the shared buffer
    - output through FPGA removes 54 Mbps limitation


Memories:
  Shared buffer (SDRAM): 256 MB
  Local memory (SBRAM): 1 MB per DSP
  Internal data memory (C6x): 512 kB per DSP
  Internal program memory (C6x)

  - DSP needs to DMA data from SDRAM into SBRAM or internal data memory
    before processing
  - accessing data in internal memory is much faster than in SBRAM


Bus bandwidth:
  MLC backplane (PCI): 25 MHz/32-bits => 800 Mbps
  Assume 2 MLC, 50% efficiency => 200 Mbps per MLC (4x54 Mbps or 5x38.8 Mbps)
                75% efficiency => 300 Mbps per MLC (6x54 Mbps or 7x38.8 Mbps)


Functional blocks:
  A PCI Bus Bridge (FPGA) connects the UBR host and the MLC.
  It performs PID remapping, time-stamping, demuxing into channel buffers.
  Same FPGA also serves as the IP interface: TP extraction from IP,
      TP assembly into IP

  The local bus connects all modules in MLC: FPGAs, shared buffer, DSPs

  IO modules (FPGA) should match with the IO daughter board

  DSP expansion bus bridge (FPGA) connects each DSP to the local bus.


Theory of Operation:
  MPEG input (Input module)
      - remap PID, time-stamping, demux input MPEG packets into Shared Buffer

  IP input (IP interface)
      - gets IP packets from Host Shared Memory thru PCI back plane,
      - strips off IP header, recover MPEG packets
      - PID remap, time-stamping, demux into Shared Buffer

  DSP
      - monitors Shared Buffer and collect statistics for each video program
      - if necessary, copy data to local memory and perform rate reduction,
        and send output MPEG packets back to Shared Buffer
      - calculate output time for each MPEG packet
      - sends scheduling table to either output module or IP interface
        depending on output interface type

  MPEG output (Output module)
      - read MPEG packet from Shared Buffer,
      - PCR correction,
      - output packet according to schedule

  IP output (IP interface)
      - read MPEG packet from Shared Buffer
      - PCR correction
      - assemble MPEG packet into IP, add IP header
      - send IP packet to Shared Memory in Host thru PCI back plane
        according to schedule


