NorthStar

New features (over Heavenly):
  - VBR multiplexing
  - Rate reduction
  - Statistical multiplexing
  - DPI
  - QuadQAM support
      - single output up to 160 Mbps, 1 QuadQAM output per MLC
  - MPTS input
      - MPTS input over IP added
  - Multicast support
  - Data insertion / encapsulation
      - Data: teletext/subtitling, EPG, DVB/ATSC compliant PSI/SI,
              CA ECMs and EMMs, data enhanced content (ATVEF), etc
      - mux into output ASI stream


Shared data structures
  - Channel buffer
  - packet info buffer
  - packet info write pointer

  - mux Stat
  - rcTrack
  - rcEState


Channel Buffer
  - May hold one ore more PID streams
  - size configurable by DSP
  - currently three sizes are planned for HD video, SD video and others

MIPS/DSP Message Interface

DSP: Tx/Rx Tasks
MIPS: Message Handler (MH)


Major DSP tasks
  - Stat collector
      - collect statistics and send it to Stat Mux
  - Stat Mux
      - scheduling
      - send bit allocation decision to rate conversion task
      - send schedule table to output task
  - Rate Convertor
      - performs rate conversion
  - Output
      - construct ouptut command to output module


Memory Pool Allocation
  Stat Colletor DSP:
    - 2 to 3 per MLC
    - 24 MB per DSP

  Rate Convert DSP:
    - 7 to 8 per MLC
    - 4 MB per DSP

  Stat Mux DSP:
    - 1 per MLC
    - 40 MB per DSP



PID tables (in FPGA)
  Table 1
    - 8k entries (13-bit)
    - input and remapped PID
    - channel buffer index
  Table 2
    - 1k entries (1024 CBs)
    - start address, size, write pointers, etc.

  

StatColl DSP
  StatColl DSP image contains three modules:
    Input Module (Frank Liu)
    StatCollector Module: Demux & PreParser tasks (Pierre Seigneurbieux)
    PSI Snooping Module (Fengming)

  Input Module 
    - Poll all channel buffers periodically for input packets
    - Perform clock drift compensation
    - Process up to 128 TPs per CB
    - Build pktInfo for each TP in passThru CB, send them back to Shared Buffer
    - Update StatMux on pktInfo buffer and PicStat buffer write pointers
    - Interface to Demux for non-passThru CB
    - Program PID tables


Task communication
  Input/Stat coll will wake up every 20 msec.  After finish its task, it will
  update StatMux.

  StatMux will wake up every 1/4 sec.  It will process 1/4 sec worth of data.
  Processed pictures will be past to rate convertor.

  Rate convertor will update statMux on its progress every 30 msec.

